==English==
===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek [[κάθαρσις]] ([[cleansing]], [[purging]]), [[καθαρίζω]] (To [[clean]])
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kəˈθʌɹsɪs/}}
===Noun===
'''catharsis'''
#(''medicine'') [[purge|Purging]] of the [[digestive]] [[system]]
#A [[release]] of [[emotional]] [[tension]] after an [[overwhelm]]ing [[vicarious]] experience, resulting in the purging or [[purification]] of the emotions, as through watching a [[drama]]tic production (especially a [[tragedy]]). [[Coined]] in this sense by [[Aristotle]].
#A release of emotional tension to the same effect, more widely.
#(''psychology'') A [[therapeutic]] [[technique]] to relieve tension
